<naming-conventions>

<title>Naming Conventions</title>

<rules>
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for classes and types
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- Start variable names with lowercase letter
- Start class and type names with uppercase letter
- Constants must be all uppercase with underscores between words
</rules>

<examples>
<example type="good">
```typescript
// Variables
const userName = "John";
let isActive = true;
const userAge = 25;

// Functions
function calculateTotal() { }
const getUserData = () => { };
async function fetchApiData() { }

// Classes
class UserAccount { }
class PaymentProcessor { }
class DatabaseConnection { }

// Types
type UserProfile = { };
interface ApiResponse { }
enum UserRole { }

// Constants
const MAX_RETRY_ATTEMPTS = 3;
const API_BASE_URL = "https://api.example.com";
const DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS = 5000;
```
</example>
